Endothoracic endoesophageal pull-through operation. A new approach to cancers of the esophagus and proximal stomach.
 Many thoracic surgeons have expressed concern about the complications inherent in transhiatal esophagectomy without thoracotomy.
 The technique of endothoracic endoesophageal pull-through uses a mucosal coring of normal esophagus beyond the tumor and leaves a muscular tube through which the substitute organ is passed.
 Mediastinal hemorrhage, tracheal injury, and chylothorax are eliminated.
